headline: Sysco stock edges lower after holding earnings forecast steady
summary: Sysco Corp. (SYY) shares are under pressure after the food service company reported a fiscal second quarter earnings beat, but reaffirmed its initial full-year earnings forecast. Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton outline what investors need to know on Market Domination. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: Food supplier Sysco keeps full-year forecasts unchanged despite quarterly beat
summary: Sales in the company's food service business in the U.S., which caters to offices, amusement parks, casinos, bowling alleys and movie theaters, rose 4.1% in the quarter ended Dec. 28 from a year ago, slower than the 4.6% year-on-year increase in the prior quarter.  Higher costs of products such as dairy and poultry have also pressured Sysco's quarterly margins, leading to a 11-basis-point decrease to 18.1% in the second quarter.  Sysco is a distributor of a range of food items from meats and fresh produce to frozen foods and baked goods.
